{"type":"message","id":"cd2083ff","parentId":"42a5c7a2","timestamp":"2026-05-03T12:48:17.912Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me think about what's happening here. The user is saying they sent a message from Feishu and it didn't come through to the current conversation. They're asking if Feishu messages should arrive in the current conversation.\n\nThe issue is that the current session appears to be a webchat direct conversation (channel: \"webchat\", provider: \"webchat\"). Feishu messages might be routing to a different session.\n\nLooking at the architecture:\n- Current session: webchat direct\n- Feishu might be a separate channel\n\nThe user is asking if messages from Feishu should arrive in the current webchat session. The answer depends on how OpenClaw routes messages. If Feishu is configured as a separate channel with its own session routing, messages might not appear in the webchat session.\n\nLet me think about this more carefully. The user seems to be testing if Feishu integration is working by sending messages from Feishu and checking if they appear in the current webchat conversation. If they don't appear, it could mean:\n1. Feishu is routing to a different session\n2. The Feishu integration isn't properly configured to route to this session\n3. Something else is wrong with the routing\n\nThe user just said \"我发了以及\" which seems incomplete - maybe they meant \"我发了一条\" (I sent one message).\n\nLet me just respond to acknowledge and ask them to confirm if the Feishu message appeared in this webchat session.\n","thinkingSignature":"57109dde30299c9e6554e151ef87a12e6f388e2e745d122186dbe8be98d6db21"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j6lkwdf0q6tx_1","name":"session_status","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":230,"output":317,"cacheRead":27744,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28291,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0