{"type":"message","id":"cb18fc1a","parentId":"a8517807","timestamp":"2026-05-03T12:49:41.658Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"User is saying they sent a message from Feishu but I'm not receiving it. This is still the same issue - Feishu messages are not coming through to this session. Let me think about what could be wrong.\n\nThe user is asking if messages from Feishu go to the current conversation. Based on the config, the gateway is bound to loopback only (127.0.0.1), which means it's not accessible externally. This could be why Feishu messages aren't reaching the gateway.\n\nBut actually, the issue might be simpler - the user might need to check if the Feishu channel is properly configured in OpenClaw. The lark-cli is installed and configured, but that doesn't automatically mean OpenClaw's Feishu channel plugin is set up to receive messages.\n\nLet me suggest checking the OpenClaw feishu configuration. The user should verify that:\n1. The Feishu channel plugin is enabled in OpenClaw\n2. The webhook/endpoint is properly configured in Feishu developer console\n\nActually, looking at the status output from earlier:\n- Gateway: bind=loopback (127.0.0.1), port=18789\n- This means the gateway only listens on localhost\n- For Feishu to send messages, it needs to be accessible from the internet (or at least from Feishu's servers)\n\nBut wait - this is a complex setup issue. Let me just honestly tell the user what I observe - that I'm not receiving the Feishu messages and they might need to check the channel configuration.\n","thinkingSignature":"b3451acbf45a473a614f375a97eaf3360ad67260c485a8106e9a82889f22a6d8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_t4erbwef3vsf_1","name":"session_status","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34,"output":336,"cacheRead":28960,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29330,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"