{"type":"message","id":"8d970a00","parentId":"a5178e7a","timestamp":"2026-05-03T12:49:52.623Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"User is saying they sent messages from Feishu but I'm not receiving them here. This is the core issue - Feishu messages should route to this conversation but they're not appearing.\n\nLet me think about what might be wrong:\n1. The Feishu bot is configured and bound (identity: bot)\n2. Gateway was restarted\n3. But messages from Feishu are not reaching this webchat session\n\nThe issue could be that the bot identity doesn't support receiving DMs - bot tokens might only work for sending, not receiving. Or the channel configuration might be incorrect.\n\nActually, looking at the docs flow: we set up lark-cli with bot identity. The issue is that bot identity has limitations - it can only send messages, not receive them in a conversational manner. To receive messages, you'd typically need user-default identity or a different setup.\n\nWait - let me re-read the context. The user is asking \"从飞书发消息，是到当前对话吗\" - \"When sending from Feishu, does it go to the current conversation?\"\n\nAnd they confirmed they sent but nothing is arriving.\n\nThe fundamental issue might be that:\n1. We're in a webchat session\n2. Feishu channel might not be routed to this session\n3. Or bot-only identity can't receive messages back\n\nLet me check what channels are actually configured and active.\n","thinkingSignature":"5d9be02642bf2702b09506a92186e0f17a63843fe82f6132e61505b7955ff5aa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0po14py6sqek_1","name":"session_status","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":237,"output":293,"cacheRead":28960,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29490,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777812583755,"responseId":"06467768ea510154f2bf45f1cd5d421c"}}
