{"type":"message","id":"81f33e9f","parentId":"7c34e3ba","timestamp":"2026-05-03T12:50:41.499Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me think about what's happening here. The user is trying to set up Feishu integration with OpenClaw. They chose \"机器人身份\" (bot identity), completed the binding process, but when they send messages from Feishu, nothing comes through to this conversation.\n\nLooking at the conversation flow:\n1. User chose bot identity\n2. They ran `lark-cli config bind --identity bot-only` successfully\n3. `lark-cli auth status` showed `identity: \"bot\"` \n4. They restarted the gateway\n5. They tried sending from Feishu but nothing received here\n6. They restarted the gateway again\n7. They're still not receiving Feishu messages\n\nThe issue seems to be that while the lark-cli is configured correctly for bot identity, the OpenClaw gateway itself may not have the Feishu channel properly connected or configured to route messages to this session.\n\nLet me check if there's a Feishu plugin or channel configuration issue. The user mentioned earlier seeing a warning about openclaw-weixin, but that's a different plugin. They need the @openclaw/feishu plugin to be properly configured.\n\nSince this is a webchat session right now, I might not be receiving the Feishu messages at all - they could be going to a different session or endpoint.\n\nLet me tell the user what I think is happening and suggest checking the gateway configuration to see how Feishu messages should be routed.","thinkingSignature":"7da40afb93d048467e295649472a411e4362ad412f5d4e7013b0efe8cacf5468"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0g9nsb9hqmww_1","name":"session_status","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":218,"output":313,"cacheRead":29600,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30131,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":177781