{"type":"message","id":"8c613631","parentId":"c634bab1","timestamp":"2026-05-03T12:59:43.958Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me understand the situation. The user wants to use Feishu (Lark) to communicate with me through OpenClaw. Currently they're using web UI only, but they want to set up Feishu as a channel so they can message me from Feishu.\n\nLooking at the context:\n1. User has Feishu CLI installed (lark-cli)\n2. The bot identity is configured (identity: \"bot\")\n3. The user wants messages from Feishu to route to me (KIIT)\n\nThe problem is that lark-cli is a tool for the AI to call Feishu APIs, but it doesn't automatically make the AI receive messages from Feishu. For that, OpenClaw needs to have a Feishu channel plugin configured and running.\n\nLet me check the current OpenClaw config to see what channel plugins are configured. I need to look at the Feishu plugin configuration.\n\nThe user mentioned earlier seeing warnings about `openclaw-weixin` plugin. Let me check if there's a Feishu channel plugin that needs to be configured.\n\nLet me look at the config to understand what's set up.","thinkingSignature":"f6f41e2a58ad5665256bd6371563433133757e78a2d79314c7674d691f87af13"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n明白了。你现在用 web UI 和我对话，但想从飞书发消息也能找到我。\n\n这需要 OpenClaw 配置飞书 channel 插件，让网关能接收飞书消息。让我看一下当前配置。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lk7c6j9pk68s_1","name":"session_status","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":225,"output":292,"cacheRead":32288,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32805,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777813174834,"responseId":"064679b79157e257ebd933b7d8537ea5"}}
