{"type":"message","id":"de381833","parentId":"d656a855","timestamp":"2026-05-03T12:59:57.590Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me think about this. The user wants feishu to work. They installed lark-cli and bound it. Now they're saying they can send messages from feishu but this webchat doesn't receive them.\n\nThe issue is likely that the Feishu channel plugin isn't configured or connected to this agent. The user is using webchat directly, not through any channel. For Feishu messages to come to this agent, the Feishu plugin needs to be properly configured in OpenClaw.\n\nLet me check the OpenClaw config to see how channels are set up. But since I can't run exec directly and don't have the right tools, let me just tell the user what I understand.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully - the user installed lark-cli for the AI agent functionality (using it as a tool), but that's different from the Feishu channel plugin that routes messages FROM Feishu TO this agent.\n\nFor receiving Feishu messages, OpenClaw needs a Feishu channel plugin configured. The user seems to want messages from Feishu to route to this KIIT agent.\n\nLet me think about what the user needs:\n1. lark-cli is installed - this is for AI to call Feishu APIs (done ✓)\n2. Feishu channel plugin - this is for receiving messages FROM Feishu users\n\nThe second part is what's missing. The user needs to configure the Feishu channel in OpenClaw. But I don't have enough info to do this - I don't know their specific Feishu app credentials or how they set it up.\n\nLet me just explain this to the user and ask for what I need.","thinkingSignature":"ebd425090159417744f6d17c4a099ab2378df65f8102d712c440cec054d86ae9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_komiwvuctdib_1","name":"session_status","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":229,"output":355,"cacheRead":32480,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33064,