{"type":"message","id":"57983a3f","parentId":"0b3896c0","timestamp":"2026-05-03T13:00:21.032Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to set up Feishu integration. They've been trying to get Feishu working. Let me check the current configuration and what needs to be done.\n\nBased on the conversation:\n1. User installed lark-cli\n2. User selected \"机器人身份\" (bot identity)\n3. They ran `lark-cli config bind --identity bot-only` \n4. The auth status shows `identity: \"bot\"` but `note: \"No user logged in. Only bot (tenant) identity is available for API calls.\"`\n5. User sends messages from Feishu but nothing comes through to current conversation\n6. User is using web UI (not any channel), wants Feishu to work\n\nThe key issue is: the user wants to receive messages from Feishu in their current web chat session. But currently Feishu messages go to a separate session/channel, not to the web UI session.\n\nTo make Feishu work with OpenClaw, the bot needs to be properly configured as a channel in OpenClaw. Let me check the current config and see what's needed.\n\nActually, looking at the situation - the user installed `lark-cli` but that's for the AI to call Feishu APIs. For Feishu to send messages TO the AI, OpenClaw needs a Feishu channel plugin configured.\n\nLet me check the current config to see if there's a Feishu channel configured.","thinkingSignature":"8c9a6d99d4f702419d3eb46283fbee65be8810db0a12a690dda0c8d304bc5ebc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_je7hforsuqpl_1","name":"session_status","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":208,"output":310,"cacheRead":32896,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33414,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777813204942,"responseId":"064679d5da7fa72acd6c49d381f0dcfd"}}
