{"type":"message","id":"7db537f4","parentId":"be86d163","timestamp":"2026-05-03T13:00:38.852Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me understand the situation:\n\n1. HALEI is using web UI to chat with me, no channel configured\n2. They want Feishu to work - when they send messages from Feishu, it should come to this conversation\n3. They've already installed lark-cli and bound it as bot identity\n4. But messages from Feishu are not arriving here\n\nThe issue is that the current session is via webchat (provider: webchat), not Feishu. So even if Feishu is configured, messages won't route to this webchat session unless the gateway is configured to route Feishu messages to the webchat session.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The user wants Feishu to work as a channel. They've installed lark-cli but that doesn't automatically enable Feishu as a messaging channel in OpenClaw.\n\nFor OpenClaw to receive Feishu messages, you typically need:\n1. Feishu webhook/bot configuration in OpenClaw\n2. OR use the lark-cli with a running server\n\nBut actually, looking at the user's setup - they seem to want to use Feishu as a channel. Let me check what the current gateway config looks like to understand what's missing.\n\nActually, the user said they're using web UI to chat with me, no channel. So they want to ADD Feishu as a channel. But for Feishu to work, you need proper OpenClaw configuration with a Feishu app/bot token.\n\nThe lark-cli installation is separate from OpenClaw's Feishu channel integration. lark-cli is for API calls, not for receiving messages.\n\nLet me think about what the user actually needs. They want:\n- Feishu messages to reach me (KIIT)\n\nFor this to work, OpenClaw needs to be configured with Feishu channel. The current config seems to only have webchat.\n\n\nI need to check the actual gateway configuration to see what's currently set up and what Feishu credentials or tokens might be missing.","thinkingSignature":"0642