{"type":"message","id":"23833546","parentId":"e93e01d5","timestamp":"2026-05-03T13:01:20.938Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me think about this. The user wants me to configure Feishu so that messages sent from Feishu arrive in the current conversation. \n\nLooking at the context:\n1. The user is using WebUI (webchat) to talk to me - no channel configured\n2. They want Feishu to work - messages from Feishu should come to this session\n3. We've been trying to set up lark-cli\n\nThe issue is that the user is using WebUI directly. For Feishu messages to route to this session, the gateway needs to be configured with the Feishu channel. The lark-cli is for AI agents to call Feishu APIs, but for receiving messages from Feishu, we need the @openclaw/feishu plugin to be properly configured.\n\nLet me check the current config to see what Feishu configuration exists. I need to use gateway config.get to see the current channels configuration.\n\nActually, looking at the setup instructions more carefully - lark-cli is for the AI agent to use Feishu APIs. But for receiving messages FROM Feishu INTO this conversation, we need the OpenClaw Feishu channel plugin to be configured and enabled.\n\nLet me think about what's needed:\n1. The @openclaw/feishu plugin needs to be installed and configured\n2. The feishu channel needs to be set up in the gateway config\n3. The gateway needs to be restarted\n\nLet me check the current gateway config to see what's there.","thinkingSignature":"4de1b962e55225893ea9d9427ee07b4ee9464758f95b8aebf0288db441758fdd"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n明白了。你用 WebUI 和我对话，但飞书消息要接入这个会话，需要在网关配置里启用飞书频道。\n\n让我看看当前配置。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7osi0hfjjmr0_1","name":"session_status","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":211,"output":358,"cacheRead":33888,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34457,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrit