{"type":"message","id":"15d3ce53","parentId":"ddaa6aeb","timestamp":"2026-05-03T13:01:39.092Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to set up Feishu integration. They've been trying to configure it but messages from Feishu aren't reaching the current conversation.\n\nLet me understand the situation:\n- User is using WebUI (webchat) to talk to me\n- User wants Feishu to work - when they send messages from Feishu, it should come to this conversation\n- They've installed lark-cli and configured it with bot identity\n- The auth status shows `identity: \"bot\"` which is correct for bot-only mode\n\nThe key issue is: Feishu integration needs to be configured as a channel in OpenClaw. The user is using WebUI now, but wants Feishu messages to route to this session.\n\nLooking at the Feishu doc that was pasted earlier - it's about configuring `lark-cli` for OpenClaw/Hermes. But for Feishu to work as a channel that routes messages to this agent, we need to configure the Feishu channel plugin in OpenClaw.\n\nLet me check what channel configuration is needed. The user needs to set up the Feishu channel so messages from Feishu bot can be routed to this agent session.\n\nActually, looking at the context more carefully - the user installed `@larksuite/cli` and did `lark-cli config bind --identity bot-only`. But for OpenClaw to receive Feishu messages, we need the `openclaw-feishu` channel plugin configured.\n\nLet me read the feishu-doc skill to understand how to configure this properly.","thinkingSignature":"aab9d7370625395fa80e651bdb22a6632227179477d2f09a4032913d3ec3a66f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fwzioovih84u_1","name":"session_status","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":225,"output":334,"cacheRead":34272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34831,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1