{"type":"message","id":"afb011c4","parentId":"d01e1594","timestamp":"2026-05-03T13:01:59.077Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me think about what's happening here. The user wants to set up Feishu so that when they send messages from Feishu, it routes to this current conversation.\n\nThe issue is that they're using web UI to chat with me (KIIT), but they want Feishu messages to also come through. The current setup has lark-cli configured with bot identity, but there's no Feishu channel configured in OpenClaw.\n\nLooking at the situation:\n1. The user is using webchat (current session) to talk to me\n2. They want Feishu integration working\n3. lark-cli is configured but not the actual Feishu channel in OpenClaw\n\nThe user said earlier they want to set it up so when they send from Feishu, it goes to the current conversation. This is about routing Feishu messages to the webchat session.\n\nActually, looking at the runtime info:\n- channel: webchat\n- provider: webchat\n- surface: webchat\n- chat_type: direct\n\nThis is a direct webchat. To receive Feishu messages in the same session, OpenClaw needs a Feishu channel configured. But the user mentioned earlier they don't want to use any channel - they're using web UI directly.\n\nWait, I think I understand now. The user wants the Feishu CLI (lark-cli) to work WITH OpenClaw, not just be a standalone tool. They want to configure the Feishu channel properly so Feishu messages route to OpenClaw.\n\nLet me re-read the context. The user originally asked to set up lark-cli per the instructions, and they chose \"bot identity\". After binding and auth status check, the status showed bot identity was configured. Then they tried sending messages from Feishu but got no response.\n\nSo the issue is: lark-cli is configured but OpenClaw doesn't have a Feishu channel configured to receive messages. The lark-cli is a tool/CLI for making API calls, but for receiving messages, OpenClaw needs an inbound Feishu channel.\n\n\nThe user wants Feishu configured as an inbound channel so messages route to this session. But they also said \"我没有用任何channel\" - they're using web UI directly. So maybe they want both web UI and Feishu to work? Or maybe they want Feishu messages to somehow come through to the same KIIT session?\n\nI think the user might be confused about the architecture. The lark-cli is for making API calls as a bot, but for OpenClaw to receive Feishu messages, it needs an inbound Feishu channel configured separately. Let me think about what they actually need to do to make this work.\n\nActually, looking back at what they said - they want Feishu to work. So they need OpenClaw configured with a Feishu channel that receives messages. The lark-cli is already set up for bot identity, but that's separate from the inbound message handling. To receive messages in this session, OpenClaw needs an inbound Feishu channel configured. The user's comment about not using any channel suggests they might not realize they need to set up that inbound channel for Feishu to work with OpenClaw.\n","thinkingSignature":"759a0b52d8e9239a28b2f1c85a0291240f6c43f10f606091fa142a4cdaff543f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jcgveas0ilhs_1","name":"session_status","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":232,"output":681,"cacheRead":34464,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35377,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777813300427,"responseId":"06467a348079c60a60dfd9b9070f1f72"}}
