{"type":"message","id":"1cb59ea5","parentId":"139d6437","timestamp":"2026-05-03T13:02:09.778Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying they use web UI to talk to me, no channel. They want me to set up Feishu so it works. \n\nThe key issue is: the user is using web UI (direct conversation), but wants Feishu integration to work - meaning when messages come from Feishu, they should route to this conversation/session.\n\nLet me check the current configuration. The user's Feishu OpenID is ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb. They selected \"机器人身份\" (bot-only), which means identity=bot.\n\nLooking at what happened:\n- lark-cli is configured with bot identity\n- But the messages from Feishu aren't reaching this session\n\nThe issue is likely that the OpenClaw gateway needs to be configured to route Feishu messages to the agent session. The gateway is running on loopback only (127.0.0.1:18789), which is correct for local access.\n\nBut wait - the user is using web UI (openclaw-control-ui). They want Feishu messages to come through to this same session. The problem is the gateway config needs a Feishu channel plugin configured.\n\nLet me look at what needs to happen:\n1. The Feishu CLI is installed ✓\n2. Bot identity is bound ✓\n3. The gateway needs to be configured to use the Feishu channel\n\nThe user sent a URL: https://open.feishu.cn/page/cli?user_code=YBYZ-2T4F&lpv=1.0.23&ocv=1.0.23&from=cli - this was the verification URL for binding the bot.\n\nNow they need to configure OpenClaw gateway to use Feishu as a channel. The gateway config likely needs the Feishu plugin configured.\n\nLet me check the current config to see what's there.","thinkingSignature":"55391bb98d6bbac3e6e2dab937c4af4aaf9cf43c3c9dbea7624eab05782b01e8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qsvmisq3o0vb_1","name":"session_status","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":207,"output":406,"c