{"type":"message","id":"3a6b06c6","parentId":"48dd1f3e","timestamp":"2026-05-03T13:02:30.683Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying they communicate with me via web UI and don't use any channel. They want me to set up Feishu so that it works.\n\nLet me think about what they need:\n- They're using web UI (OpenClaw Control UI) to talk to me\n- They want Feishu integration working so messages from Feishu can reach me\n- I need to configure the Feishu channel in OpenClaw\n\nLooking at the conversation flow:\n1. User configured lark-cli with bot identity ✓\n2. They ran `lark-cli auth status` and got `{\"identity\": \"bot\"}` ✓\n3. They tried sending messages from Feishu but I don't receive them\n4. They重启了 gateway\n5. They're still not receiving messages\n\nThe issue is likely that the Feishu channel is not properly configured in OpenClaw's channels config. The `lark-cli` is for bot operations, but for receiving messages, OpenClaw needs a Feishu channel configured.\n\nLet me check what channels are configured. I should look at the OpenClaw config to see if Feishu is set up as a channel. From the earlier status output, I saw warnings about `openclaw-weixin` plugin, but nothing about Feishu.\n\nI need to check the gateway config to see what channels are configured. Let me use the gateway tool to check the config.\n\nActually, let me re-read the Feishu skill to understand how to configure the channel properly.\n\nWait - I don't have exec tool available in minimal mode. Let me think about what I can do.\n\nLooking at my available tools - I only have session_status. With minimal tools profile, I can't exec commands directly.\n\nBut the user is asking ME to set it up. I need to figure out how to help them. Let me check if there's a way...\n\nActually, looking at the situation:\n1. The user has `lark-cli` configured with bot identity\n2. But OpenClaw doesn't have a Feishu channel configured to RECEIVE messages\n3. The Feishu skill (feishu-doc, feishu-drive, etc.) are for document operations\n\n\n4. For MESSAGE receiving from Feishu, there needs to be a channel configuration\n\nI should explain to the user that having `lark-cli` configured is for bot operations (sending messages, accessing documents etc), but for receiving messages from Feishu, OpenClaw needs a Feishu webhook/channel setup. This is separate from `lark-cli` configuration.\n\nActually wait - looking at the original request more carefully. The user said \"飞书不行\" and \"通信终于通了\" which suggests they were trying to get Feishu working and it finally worked. Then they said \"可以了吗\" and \"绑定了\" which suggests they did something with the binding.\n\nLet me re-trace:\n1. User tried to configure something for Feishu communication\n2. They ran `lark-cli config bind --identity bot-only` and it succeeded (got `{\"identity\": \"bot\"}`)\n3. They sent messages from Feishu but I didn't receive them\n4. They restarted the gateway\n5. They sent more messages but I still didn't receive them\n\nThe issue is likely that while `lark-cli` is configured for bot operations, the OpenClaw gateway itself doesn't have a Feishu channel configured to receive incoming messages. The Feishu skill is for document operations, not for message handling.\n\nLooking at what I can actually do with limited tools - I should explain this clearly to the user rather than continuing to check status. The core problem is that `lark-cli` handles API operations but doesn't configure the gateway to receive WebSocket events from Feishu. I need to check the gateway config to understand what channel setup is actually needed here.","thinkingSignature":"7e299957d6d3db45623519ee0cd097b77d044bb5e24c77fd665eb8af676661c3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m3sn2bri3uqs_1","name":"session_status","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":214,"output":808,"cacheRead":34880,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35902,"cost":{"i