{"type":"message","id":"a8591b5e","parentId":"ca5500a4","timestamp":"2026-05-03T13:29:50.015Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me take a step back. The user is saying they're using web UI to communicate with me, and they want to set up Feishu so that when they send messages from Feishu, it routes to this current conversation.\n\nThe issue is that the user is using web UI (direct conversation with me), but they also want to be able to send messages from Feishu and have those messages appear in this same conversation.\n\nThe setup they've done with `lark-cli` (bot identity) allows the AI to send messages AS a bot, but for incoming messages FROM Feishu to route to this conversation, there needs to be a Feishu channel plugin configured in OpenClaw.\n\nLooking at the status output from earlier, there was a warning about `openclaw-weixin` plugin missing channelConfigs metadata. But the user is using Feishu, not WeChat.\n\nFor OpenClaw to receive Feishu messages, it needs the `@openclaw/feishu` plugin properly configured. Looking at the skills available, there are several feishu-related skills:\n- feishu-doc\n- feishu-drive\n- feishu-perm\n- feishu-wiki\n\nBut these seem to be for interacting with Feishu documents, not for receiving messages. The skill I should read is probably one of these or a specific feishu channel skill.\n\nLet me read the feishu-doc skill to understand the Feishu integration better. Wait, actually I should check if there's a feishu messaging/channel skill available. The user mentioned they're talking to me via web UI without any channel - so this is a direct conversation.\n\nFor Feishu to work as an inbound channel, OpenClaw needs to have the Feishu webhook/bot configured. The lark-cli is for sending messages FROM the bot. But for RECEIVING messages TO the bot, OpenClaw needs a Feishu message webhook setup.\n\nLet me think about what the user actually wants:\n1. They want to be able to chat with me via Feishu (send a message in Feishu and get a response)\n\n\n2. Currently they can only chat via web UI\n\nFor this to work, OpenClaw needs a Feishu channel plugin configured with a bot that can receive messages. The user may have set up the lark-cli for outbound messaging capabilities, but the inbound direction—where messages FROM Feishu arrive at the bot—requires proper webhook and channel configuration within OpenClaw itself.\n\nSince the user is communicating through web UI rather than a dedicated Feishu client, the messages they sent from Feishu likely aren't being routed to this agent. I need to clarify what the user means by \"from Feishu\"—whether they're sending messages through a Feishu bot interface or if there's something else happening with their message flow. the messages they're sending from Feishu should appear in this session. But since the user is communicating via web UI, those messages aren't showing up here.\n\nI should ask for clarification on what they're trying to accomplish. The user might expect that configuring the lark-cli will route all their Feishu messages to this agent, but that would require the Feishu platform to actually send the messages to OpenClaw—which needs a webhook endpoint and proper bot configuration to receive them. Let me just ask them directly what they're trying to do.","thinkingSignature":"2acc61715fd38e52757f6eaa2d577c3c4b8502071bda40bb33d3a0cadb94dc5e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p94dkso6sp4s_1","name":"session_status","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":210,"output":708,"cacheRead":39552,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40470,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777814973307,"responseId":"064680bdacfc36f0f8ff85b4c22bee7a"}}
