{"type":"message","id":"7e7d56a7","parentId":"991b0b94","timestamp":"2026-05-03T13:46:09.508Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so there's a clawpanel with a password set. The `device identity required` error is likely because the gateway was started by clawpanel and is in a secured mode.\n\nLet me think about the root cause of the communication issues. The user says messages have low success rate. Looking at the logs:\n\n1. WeChat messages ARE getting through (inbound and outbound both show OK)\n2. But the gateway is restarting frequently\n3. The event loop delays are high\n\nThe frequent restarts could be the main issue. The gateway keeps crashing/restarting, which causes messages to be lost.\n\nLet me check the service file to understand why it keeps restarting.","thinkingSignature":"4d32bb8607d862270024ae5b2b9c623494f6775e61b84a1e6c95592d29e935b6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zluakbkwjtc6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.config/systemd/user/openclaw-gateway.service"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":69879,"output":170,"cacheRead":20974,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91023,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777815962711,"responseId":"0646849b534d03b00a3f705d4aa705b3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"aef2af8c","parentId":"7e7d56a7","timestamp":"2026-05-03T13:46:09.942Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zluakbkwjtc6_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Unit]\nDescription=OpenClaw Gateway (v2026.5.2)\nAfter=network-online.target\nWants=network-online.target\nStartLimitBurst=5\nStartLimitIntervalSec=60\n\n[Service]\nExecStart=/home/halei/.n/bin/node /home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/index.js gateway --port 18789\nRestart=always\nRestartSec=5\nRestartPreventExitStatus=78\nTimeoutStopSec=30\nTimeoutStartSec=30\nSuccessExitStatus=0 143\nKillMode=control-group\nEnvironment=HOME=/home/halei\nEnvironment=TMPDIR=/tmp\nEnvironment=PATH=/home/halei/.n/bin:/home/halei/.local/bin:/home/halei/.npm-global/bin:/home/halei/bin:/home/halei/.nix-profile/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin\nEnvironment=OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PORT=18789\nEnvironment=OPENCLAW_INSECURE_AUTH=1\nEnvironment=OPENCLAW_SYSTEMD_UNIT=openclaw-gateway.service\nEnvironment=\"OPENCLAW_WINDOWS_TASK_NAME=OpenClaw Gateway\"\nEnvironment=OPENCLAW_SERVICE_MARKER=openclaw\nEnvironment=OPENCLAW_SERVICE_KIND=gateway\nEnvironment=OPENCLAW_SERVICE_VERSION=2026.5.2\n\n[Install]\nWantedBy=default.target"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":137,"aggregated":"[Unit]\nDescription=OpenClaw Gateway (v2026.5.2)\nAfter=network-online.target\nWants=network-online.target\nStartLimitBurst=5\nStartLimitIntervalSec=60\n\n[Service]\nExecStart=/home/halei/.n/bin/node /home/halei/.npm-global/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/index.js gateway --port 18789\nRestart=always\nRestartSec=5\nRestartPreventExitStatus=78\nTimeoutStopSec=30\nTimeoutStartSec=30\nSuccessExitStatus=0 143\nKillMode=control-group\nEnvironment=HOME=/home/halei\nEnvironment=TMPDIR=/tmp\nEnvironment=PATH=/home/halei/.n/bin:/home/halei/.local/bin:/home/halei/.npm-global/bin:/home/halei/bin:/home/halei/.nix-profile/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin\nEnvironment=OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PORT=18789\nEnvironment=OPENCLAW_INSECURE_AUTH=1\nEnvironment=OPENCLAW_SYSTEMD_UNIT=openclaw-gateway.service\nEnvironment=\"OPENCLAW_WINDOWS_TASK_NAME=OpenClaw Gateway\"\nEnvironment=OPENCLAW_SERVICE_MARKER=openclaw\nEnvironment=OPENCLAW_SERVICE_KIND=gateway\nEnvironment=OPENCLAW_SERVICE_VERSION=2026.5.2\n\n[Install]\nWantedBy=default.target","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777815969941}}
{"type":"message","id":"6adc0b6e","parentId":"aef2af8c","timestamp":"2026-05-03T13:46:20.383Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see `Restart=always` which means the service keeps restarting. And `OPENCLAW_INSECURE_AUTH=1` is set. \n\nThe issue is that the gateway keeps restarting. The device identity issue seems to happen after each restart. This might be because after the config got corrupted/truncated during our earlier edits, the gateway is now in a bad state.\n\nWait - the `clawpanel-device-key.json` exists. Let me look at what device identity the gateway is actually getting.\n\nActually, I think the core issue is the repeated restarts. When the gateway restarts, it disconnects all channel connections (Feishu, WeChat). When it reconnects, there might be a window where messages are lost.\n \nThe event loop delays are concerning too - those large max values suggest the system is under heavy load. The gateway was likely bricked by the config edits earlier, where we accidentally created malformed JSON that got rolled back, but the restart cycle itself could have triggered a cascade of failures.\n\nI should restart the gateway once more and verify whether the device identity issue persists or if it's resolved now that things have stabilized.","thinkingSignature":"431ef92661d9ecced3548c6ca5afc24440c4d0e7d31a1992ca9fd7be4ebc376e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4lv9ucofdkd4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"systemctl --user restart openclaw-gateway 2>&1; sleep 5; systemctl --user status openclaw-gateway 2>&1 | head -20","yieldMs":12000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":70360,"output":301,"cacheRead":20974,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91635,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777815969954,"responseId":"064684a2a9f152248785d2c7e4488e68"}}
