{"type":"message","id":"56cd75da","parentId":"2da0f3be","timestamp":"2026-05-03T13:53:44.680Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so `openclaw status --deep` uses the gateway connection (WS) and fails with \"device identity required\". But `openclaw sessions` works. Let me figure out why.\n\nThe difference might be that `openclaw sessions` uses the local session store file directly (I saw \"Session store: /home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json\"), while `openclaw status --deep` tries to connect to the gateway via WebSocket.\n\nActually, looking at the `openclaw sessions` output, it listed sessions successfully. But the gateway connection fails. This is very strange.\n\nLet me check the sessions file to see the feishu session.","thinkingSignature":"e399ed0297d89f64e98c4700847e699858f110ba643ce114c1cd9cb607dac269"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v2u0r0q1m1tm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nsessions = json.load(open('/home/halei/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json'))\nfeishu = [k for k in sessions if 'feishu' in k.lower()]\nprint('Feishu sessions:', feishu)\nif feishu:\n    for k in feishu[:3]:\n        print(k, '->', sessions[k].get('lastTouchedAt','?'))\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":71082,"output":259,"cacheRead":20974,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92315,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777816415810,"responseId":"064686600032d81c5d59b2978efb401d"}}
