{"type":"message","id":"ee8585ee","parentId":"fc3e2bf7","timestamp":"2026-05-03T13:54:08.928Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The feishu sessions have no last activity timestamps - they've been inactive. And `lastMessageAt` and `lastTouchedAt` are both None, which means they haven't been touched.\n\nThis tells me the feishu channel is configured but the sessions are stale/inactive. The gateway might be having trouble routing messages to/from feishu because the sessions are stale.\n\nNow let me think about the overall problem. The user is saying that messages from Feishu and WeChat have very low success rate. The common issues are:\n\n1. Gateway CPU 70%+ - very high\n2. Gateway memory 568MB - high\n3. Event loop delay reaching 2000ms+\n\n\n4. Sessions for both channels appear stale with no recent activity timestamps\n\nI suspect the gateway is so overloaded that even when channels successfully receive incoming messages, the gateway can't process them in time before timing out. The real bottleneck seems to be the resource exhaustion rather than the channels themselves failing to receive messages. The `openclaw sessions` command works through the file store, but the gateway might be too overwhelmed to actually process incoming requests from Feishu and WeChat properly.\n\nI'm also noticing that the gateway randomly returns \"device identity required\" errors on some WS connections, which suggests it's cycling between states or struggling to maintain consistent connectivity. I should check the gateway logs to see if there's a pattern to these failures, and also examine what钉钉 is showing about the feishu integration. The high CPU usage on the gateway process (70%+) is definitely a red flag that needs investigation.\n\nLooking at the timeline more carefully, the gw process was started at 21:50 and has been running for about a minute with CPU time of only 1min 34s, so the 70% isn't as extreme as it first appeared. I should try testing whether I can actually send a message through feishu to see if the connection is functional, or try querying the gateway through the http API directly instead of dealing with the device auth complications.","thinkingSignature":"f3eb36cf6eb9c3d3d55f3092c7b12632e8f7acac51bd692ea0663a3821ec39a5"},{"type":"text","text":"飞书 session 是 stale 的（没有 lastTouchedAt）。让我查看网关当前状态和 channel 配置：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_946fg915d4i2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://127.0.0.1:18789/ 2>&1 | head -20","yieldMs":5000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":71764,"output":495,"cacheRead":20974,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93233,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777816431510,"responseId":"0646866fb1e00d4a1c00f1097ea49d9b"}}
