{"type":"message","id":"9d52b6bc","parentId":"bf04dd66","timestamp":"2026-05-03T14:06:03.571Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear now. The locally installed `@openclaw/feishu` plugin has a broken `index.js` that references a build artifact `../../redact-BDinS1q9.js` that doesn't exist. This is a version mismatch between the build and the source files.\n\nThe global (stock) feishu plugin at `~/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/feishu/` is the one that actually works. The npm global install `@openclaw/feishu` is a different, incompatible version.\n\nI need to remove the broken locally installed feishu extension and rely on the stock version. The stock feishu plugin is at `~/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/feishu/` and needs to be properly referenced.\n\n\nI should delete the broken extension at `~/.openclaw/extensions/feishu/` so the system falls back to using the stock version, then verify that the config properly references the stock plugin path.\n","thinkingSignature":"fc64aa125ec9042c30733fea41b03a673d942b174d68360c73f51bc59ad28c1c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sawov6kri9a8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/extensions/feishu/","yieldMs":3000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6777,"output":273,"cacheRead":87616,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94666,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777817148620,"responseId":"0646893da4c96aa7eb014b00e214e511"}}
