{"type":"message","id":"cb0d626d","parentId":"c23040fc","timestamp":"2026-05-03T14:14:50.547Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The staging directory has the full set of npm packages. The feishu plugin is at `~/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/feishu/`. The `redact-BDinS1q9.js` is at `~/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/`.From the feishu `index.js`: `require('../../redact-BDinS1q9.js')` - this resolves from `.../.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/feishu/` going up two levels to `.../.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/` where `redact-BDinS1q9.js` is located. So this should work from the staging directory!Let me try a different approach: instead of using the broken npm-installed version, let me copy the compiled feishu from the staging directory to the actual extensions directory. \n\nBut wait, the staging directory itself was created during an install that failed midway through—it has the compiled artifacts but those files might not actually exist on disk, which is why the feishu plugin was failing to load in the first place.\n\nThe real question is whether the staging directory's compiled output actually works. The feishu plugin loaded fine from there, but the gateway couldn't find the redact module. Let me trace through the actual paths: the gateway's extensions root is `~/.openclaw/extensions/`, and when it tries to load feishu from there, it's looking for `~/.openclaw/extensions/feishu/index.js`, but the staging directory has a completely different structure with its own node_modules path.\n\nIf I copy the staging directory's feishu to the extensions root, the relative imports would resolve correctly since the redact module would be at the expected relative path. The npm-installed version at `~/.openclaw/npm/node_modules/@openclaw/feishu/` is separate from what the gateway is trying to load, so I need to figure out which one the gateway actually uses and whether the path structure matches what the code expects.\n\nRather than keep tracing through paths, the simplest fix is to just copy the working compiled feishu from the staging directory to the extensions root.","thinkingSignature":"4b5a4c85187ef710f3cf2d6d510104f836673628cb69f27e7568cdee390cbbfa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wrg6y70ps06g_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cp -r ~/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/feishu ~/.openclaw/extensions/feishu_compiled 2>/dev/null; echo \"exit: $?\"","yieldMs":5000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":91511,"output":574,"cacheRead":20974,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":113059,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777817674695,"responseId":"06468b4b78cf28105053dc8f766e7956"}}
