{"type":"message","id":"18c21623","parentId":"454c7aed","timestamp":"2026-05-03T14:15:44.720Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now the feishu plugin has:\n- `index.js` (compiled JavaScript, not TypeScript)\n- `node_modules/` with its dependencies\n- `openclaw.plugin.json`The `index.js` should be able to find `../../redact-BDinS1q9.js` from `~/.openclaw/extensions/feishu/index.js` → `~/.openclaw/extensions/` → `~/.openclaw/extensions/redact-BDinS1q9.js`. But the redact file is at `~/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/redact-BDinS1q9.js`, not at `~/.openclaw/extensions/redact-BDinS1q9.js`.\n\n\nSo I need to place the redact file where the plugin can actually access it. The staging directory structure is `~/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/feishu/`, which means the redact file at `../../redact-BDinS1q9.js` from the feishu directory would correctly resolve to the openclaw dist folder.\n\nSince I moved feishu out of that nested structure into `~/.openclaw/extensions/feishu/`, the relative path now points to the wrong location. I should either keep feishu within the staging directory structure, or copy the entire openclaw dist folder to the right place so the paths align.","thinkingSignature":"f64f41f54556c87c30ed90da9969d1015e1926beee80a620112a73cf86e7aac4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2kv26b21edn0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Copy the openclaw dist folder to ~/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw_dist so the relative require works\ncp -r ~/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist ~/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw_dist 2>/dev/null && echo \"copied dist\"\nls ~/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw_dist/ | grep redact","yieldMs":10000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":93384,"output":413,"cacheRead":20974,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":114771,"co