{"type":"message","id":"4e314290","parentId":"897902e2","timestamp":"2026-05-03T14:16:03.320Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now from `~/.openclaw/extensions/feishu/index.js`, `../../redact-BDinS1q9.js` would resolve to `~/.openclaw/extensions/redact-BDinS1q9.js` which doesn't exist. But `../../openclaw_dist/redact-BDinS1q9.js` would work.Wait, `../../` from `~/.openclaw/extensions/feishu/` goes to `~/.openclaw/extensions/`. So `../../redact-BDinS1q9.js` would be `~/.openclaw/redact-BDinS1q9.js`. \n\nBut the file is at `~/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw_dist/redact-BDinS1q9.js`. \n\nI need to reconsider how Node.js module resolution actually works here. When the feishu package does `require('../../redact-BDinS1q9.js')`, it's looking relative to its own location in `~/.openclaw/extensions/feishu/node_modules/feishu/index.js`, so two levels up from there would be `~/.openclaw/extensions/`, not `~/.openclaw/`. That means the require path needs to reach `~/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw_dist/redact-BDinS1q9.js` instead.\n\nThe real issue is that the staging directory had the openclaw dist in the right place relative to feishu, but I've reorganized things. I should either copy the entire staging directory structure as-is, or ensure the compiled files end up in the correct nested location where feishu expects them.","thinkingSignature":"5243fbb693ef563b0276c25ba058849183e77656ce49efe6db50c703b5e7c4be"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5vpopvuee6eh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Move feishu back to the correct nested location so require paths work\nrm -rf ~/.openclaw/extensions/feishu\nmkdir -p ~/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/\ncp -r ~/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/feishu ~/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/ 2>/dev/null\n# Actually, just recrea