{"type":"message","id":"a7d57ace","parentId":"32228117","timestamp":"2026-05-03T14:23:14.483Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is `'Cannot access 'monitorAccountRuntimePromise' before initialization'` for the tts account. The `@openclaw/feishu` from npm global is 2026.5.2 but the `channels/feishu` plugin seems to be broken with this error.\n\nThis is a bug in the feishu plugin version 2026.5.2. The `monitorAccountRuntimePromise` is being accessed before initialization because the variable is declared after it's used, or there's a module initialization order issue.\n\nThe `.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb` version was a different version (2026.3.22 based on earlier output). Let me go back to using the extension's feishu plugin since it had the compiled JS files with proper bundling.\n\n\nThe real question is which feishu plugin is actually running right now. The gateway is loading from two different locations simultaneously—the global npm install and the staged install—which is causing this version conflict. Since `channels list` confirms feishu is configured and enabled, I need to trace where the active plugin is actually coming from to understand which version is causing the initialization error. The real issue is that `@openclaw/feishu@2026.5.2` is bundled as TypeScript source files that the gateway can't resolve properly—the compiled version from the extension stage works but isn't being used. The config changed to point to the npm node_modules location, but that version has source files instead of compiled output, creating a mismatch between what the gateway expects and what it can actually load.\n\nI need to either force the gateway to use the extension version that already has the compiled files, or troubleshoot the current npm version to see if it can actually run. The simplest path forward is to disable the plugins.allow restriction so both the feishu and openclaw-weixin plugins can load from their available locations, then the gateway can pick whichever version actually works.\n\nLooking at the current error, the tts channel is throwing an initialization error that's causing the whole feishu plugin to fail. This isn't a config issue—it's a code bug in the @openclaw/feishu npm package itself where something's being accessed before it's properly initialized. The fact that `channels list` still shows feishu as configured but the logs flag it as stale suggests the gateway might be running an older version of the plugin rather than the one I just installed.\n\nThe real problem is that both the kiit and tts accounts share the same feishu plugin instance, so when tts crashes due to this initialization bug, it takes down the entire feishu channel for everyone. I need to figure out which feishu plugin version is actually running and whether there's a way to isolate the accounts or fix the underlying issue.\n\nLet me check if there's a compiled version available in the extension directory that might work better.\n","thinkingSignature":"9cdcaad18677b3cc263770da1762845660acbe2a01f7b2b34f807ed6870502df"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_55x8mi4aiixn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if the symlink is working by looking at the actual feishu plugin loading\ntail -200 /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-05-03.log 2>&1 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        msg = d.get('message', '')\n        subsystem = d.get('0', '')\n        t = d.get('time', '')\n        level = d.get('_meta', {}).get('logLevelName', '')\n        if 'feishu' in str(msg).lower() or 'kiit' in str(msg).lower() or 'tts' in str(msg).lower():\n            print(f'{t} [{level}] [{subsystem}] {str(msg)[:400]}')\n    except:\n        pass\n\" 2>&1 | tail -30","yieldMs":5000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":242,"output":802,"cacheRead":111424,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112468,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777818167784,"responseId":"06468d3806dd94553c1dc5b7efb78fd9"}}
