{"type":"message","id":"be4cdb7d","parentId":"a6fdcd67","timestamp":"2026-05-03T14:23:37.845Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The current loading shows: `feishu (/home/halei/.openclaw/npm/node_modules/@openclaw/feishu/index.ts)` and `openclaw-weixin (/home/halei/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/index.ts)`. So now the feishu plugin is loading from the npm version at `~/.openclaw/npm/node_modules/@openclaw/feishu/index.ts`.\n\nBut the error is: `Cannot access 'monitorAccountRuntimePromise' before initialization` - this is a bug in the feishu plugin for the tts account.\n\nLet me look at the channel error more carefully. The error says: `[tts] channel exited: Cannot access 'monitorAccountRuntimePromise' before initialization`. This is a JavaScript runtime error - the monitor module has a `let` variable that's being accessed before it's initialized (TDZ - temporal dead zone).\n \nThe channel startup sequence differs between accounts: kiit succeeds, but tts fails when the channel starts up. The tts account is hitting this initialization error during its startup, which suggests a race condition or ordering problem in how the monitor module initializes its promises. It could be that kiit and tts are sharing a singleton state that gets corrupted, or the account channel is reusing a stale channel object from a previous session. Let me trace through the actual start sequence and check if the tts account has any lingering state from a prior deployment.\n","thinkingSignature":"4caa04d50b51ed9f8498a598f3adbae411b15943980161f7bf34dbaa61c6602f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ncjla231rn6b_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -50 /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-05-03.log 2>&1 | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        d = json.loads(line)\n        msg = d.get('message', '')\n        subsystem = d.get('0', '')\n        t = d.get('time', '')\n        level = d.get('_meta', {}).get('logLevelName', '')\n        print(f'{t} [{level}] [{subsystem}] {str(msg)[:300]}')\n    except:\n        pass\n\" 2>&1 | tail -30","yieldMs":5000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1770,"output":462,"cacheRead":111616,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":113848,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777818196166,"responseId":"06468d54c37b6e2a961158a2c4e31131"}}
