{"type":"message","id":"b12e8326","parentId":"267f42d1","timestamp":"2026-05-03T14:24:19.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the real Feishu error: `[tts] channel exited: Cannot access 'monitorAccountRuntimePromise' before initialization`. This is a bug in the `@openclaw/feishu` v2026.5.2 plugin - it has a module-level variable initialization order issue with `monitorAccountRuntimePromise`.\n\nThe current running version has `@openclaw/feishu` from npm global, which is v2026.5.2, and it has this bug. The staged version (`.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb`) had v2026.3.22 which was the working version.\n\n\nBut that earlier version had a different problem - it couldn't find the `redact-BDinS1q9.js` module. The error message indicates that `setup-entry.js` is loading `index.js` as a module, but `index.js` depends on a file that's missing from the same directory level.\n\nThe relative path `../../redact-BDinS1q9.js` from `extensions/feishu/index.js` would actually resolve to the root `dist` folder, where that file does exist. So the module resolution should work if they're being loaded as siblings in the same context.\n\nBut then I noticed something about the npm-installed feishu version - it doesn't have a `main` or `types` field in its package.json, which is suspicious. If it's a TypeScript package with no build output specified, the runtime must be using a bundler like esbuild to compile the TypeScript on-the-fly when the loader processes it. The current setup is using `feishu` from npm (v2026.5.2) with a symlink, which causes the channel to crash with \"Cannot access 'monitorAccountRuntimePromise' before initialization\". However, the `.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb` version fails because it can't find `../../redact-BDinS1q9.js`. Let me try creating a proper bundled copy of the `openclaw-lark` package into the extensions directory, since that's a known working plugin location.\n\nLooking at `openclaw-lark`, it has a `skills` directory but no `index.js` file, so it's not structured as a standard plugin. I'm wondering if I should try installing `@openclaw/feishu` globally and explicitly setting its path in the config, but the plugin system seems to auto-discover plugins from certain locations. The working version from the install stage (`v2026.3.22`) likely has compiled JavaScript files with a proper `index.js` that doesn't depend on the sourcemap-based requires I'm seeing in the newer version. Let me explore installing a compatible version or checking if there's a way to use the compiled version directly.\n\nThe real issue might be that the feishu plugin is trying to use a relative path to a redact module that's in the main openclaw `dist` folder, but the plugin's `index.js` in the extensions directory doesn't have access to that relative path. Looking at the loader path, `~/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/feishu/index.js` references `../../redact-BDinS1q9.js`, which would resolve to `~/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/redact-BDinS1q9.js` - that file exists at the right location.\n\nBut when the gateway tries to load from `~/.openclaw/extensions/feishu/index.js` (a symlink to the same path), the relative path `../../redact-BDinS1q9.js` would resolve to `~/.openclaw/extensions/redact-BDinS1q9.js` instead, which doesn't exist. The working version has this file at `~/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/redact-BDinS1q9.js` in the same directory, so the real solution is to copy the compiled feishu plugin with all its dependencies into the right location, then modify the config to point `feishu` to that directory instead of relying on auto-discovery.\n","thinkingSignature":"d5f645e8f4e5c97bc0d96e3b639552fc8a7237cd77aa35a3bbfc1982034542b8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cg1opqwof3x1_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Create a bundled copy of feishu with correct relative paths\nrm -rf ~/.openclaw/extensions/feishu_bundle\nmkdir -p ~/.openclaw/extensions/feishu_bundle\n# Copy from the working staged location\ncp -r ~/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist/extensions/feishu/* ~/.openclaw/extensions/feishu_bundle/\n# Copy the dist folder so the relative require works\ncp -r ~/.openclaw/extensions/.openclaw-install-stage-KKwmxb/node_modules/openclaw/dist ~/\necho \"done\"\nls ~/.openclaw/extensions/feishu_bundle/","yieldMs":5000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2250,"output":1042,"cacheRead":113344,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":116636,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777818219714,"responseId":"06468d6c2005314712872f9248735500"}}
